The Smartsheet Model Context Protocol (MCP) server is an integration layer that allows MCP-compliant AI clients—such as Claude, ChatGPT, and Cursor—to interact directly with Smartsheet data using natural language [1][2][3]. It bridges Smartsheet’s REST API and AI models, enabling users to query, summarize, and modify sheets, rows, and workspaces while respecting existing user permissions [1][3][4].

To use it, you need a Smartsheet Business or Enterprise plan and an MCP-compliant AI tool [3]. Configuration involves registering the server in your AI client's settings using the appropriate regional endpoint (e.g., https://mcp.smartsheet.com) and authenticating via OAuth 2.0 or a personal API token [5][3].

Example configuration for a `settings.json` file:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "smartsheet-mcp": {
      "httpUrl": "https://mcp.smartsheet.com",
      "headers": {
        "Authorization": "Bearer ${SMARTSHEET_API_TOKEN}"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

Once connected, you can use tools like `get_sheet_summary`, `search`, and row-level operations to manage data [5][6][7]. The server optimizes payloads to lower token costs and provides AI with rich metadata for context-aware responses [3][4].
